{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RRwotLUrtbrHaDXHEctkwE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture of all non-default settings:\n\n1. **elasticsearch.yml** (via `es-config` ConfigMap):\n   - `node.attr.tier: hot` — custom node attribute, non-default. This would need to be removed from the ConfigMap and nodes would need to be restarted.\n\n2. **Index `audit-index`**:\n   - `number_of_shards: 3` — non-default (default is 1). IMMUTABLE — cannot change without deleting and recreating the index.\n   - `routing.allocation.require.tier: hot` — explicit allocation filter, non-default. \n\nThe other routing settings can be removed via API, and the tier preference setting appears to be auto-applied ES 8.x behavior but was explicitly configured. There are no custom ILM policies to worry about, and cluster settings are already at defaults. Now I need to write a rollback script that removes the routing allocation filters from the index and handles the ConfigMap changes.\n\nActually, I should reconsider the tier preference setting — in ES 8.x, this gets automatically applied when there's no ILM policy managing the index, so it might not have been an explicit non-default configuration. But since the task specifies reverting non-default settings, I need to check whether this was actually set explicitly or just auto-applied by the system.\n\nThe key non-default settings I need to address are the shard count on the audit index (which can't be changed without reindexing), the routing allocation requirement for the hot tier, and the node attribute in the Elasticsearch configuration. I'm starting to write a rollback script that will systematically revert these settings.\n\nWriting rollback script... Writing rollback script... Writing shell commands... Both `_tier_preference` and `routing.allocation.require.tier` are routing allocation settings, but they work differently. The `_tier_preference` set to `data_content` is actually Elasticsearch's default for new indices in 8.x when no ILM policy is present, whereas `routing.allocation.require.tier: hot` is explicitly non-default and forces allocation only to hot-tier nodes. Since all nodes have `tier: hot` set, I need to reconsider whether the tier preference is actually a meaningful user configuration or just a system default.\n\nThe key insight is that `node.attr.tier: hot` is a static setting in elasticsearch.yml, so removing it from the ConfigMap and restarting the pods is how to revert it. However, this creates a sequencing problem—if I remove the node attribute first, the index's `routing.allocation.require.tier: hot` filter will break because no nodes will have that tier attribute anymore. I need to remove the index-level routing filter first, then remove the node attribute.\n\nI'm going to write a rollback script that handles this in the correct order.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":670,"cache_read_input_tokens":37316,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":670},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a5b4a78-ed46-4e06-8aac-06a06e5ca78c","uuid":"19f7e674-82bd-4a16-8f86-21885a4da916","request_id":"req_011Cc2f15ZEaGo4VX93pwBqg"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RRwotLUrtbrHaDXHEctkwE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Non-default settings found:\n- `audit-index`: `number_of_shards=3` (default 1, immutable), `routing.allocation.require.tier=hot` (custom filter), `_tier_preference=data_content` (explicitly set)\n- `es-config` ConfigMap: `node.attr.tier: hot` (static node attribute, needs pod restart to revert)\n- Cluster settings: none (already empty)\n- ILM policies: all are built-in managed policies, nothing custom\n\nNow I'll write the rollback script and store it as a ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":670,"cache_read_input_tokens":37316,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":670},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a5b4a78-ed46-4e06-8aac-06a06e5ca78c","uuid":"6266ff60-c232-4b4b-b76e-070510929ca9","request_id":"req_011Cc2f15ZEaGo4VX93pwBqg"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RRwotLUrtbrHaDXHEctkwE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VmH4yVuDpcSXWgh3BxYyjJ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/rollback.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# rollback.sh — revert non-default Elasticsearch settings to cluster defaults\n#\n# NON-DEFAULT SETTINGS CATALOGUED (2026-06-14):\n#   Index 'audit-index':\n#     index.number_of_shards                    = 3        (default: 1 — IMMUTABLE, see note below)\n#     index.routing.allocation.require.tier      = hot      (default: unset)\n#     index.routing.allocation.include._tier_preference = data_content (default: unset)\n#   Node config (es-config ConfigMap / elasticsearch.yml):\n#     node.attr.tier                             = hot      (default: unset)\n#   Cluster settings (persistent/transient):\n#     (none — already empty)\n#   ILM policies:\n#     (none — all policies are Elasticsearch built-in managed policies)\n#\n# DO NOT RUN WITHOUT REVIEW.\n# The live cluster currently depends on these settings.\n# Execute only during an approved maintenance window.\n#\n# Prerequisites: kubectl configured to reach the elasticsearch namespace,\n# and curl available in the curl-test pod (used for API calls).\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nES_SVC=\"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200\"\nNS=\"elasticsearch\"\nCURL_POD=\"curl-test\"\n\n# Helper: run a curl command inside the cluster via the curl-test pod\nes_curl() {\n  kubectl -n \"${NS}\" exec \"${CURL_POD}\" -- curl -s \"$@\"\n}\n\necho \"===================================================================\"\necho \" Elasticsearch Rollback Script\"\necho \" Generated: 2026-06-14 | Cluster: es-cluster (namespace: ${NS})\"\necho \"===================================================================\"\necho \"\"\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# STEP 1 — Remove custom shard allocation filters from 'audit-index'\n#\n# 'routing.allocation.require.tier=hot' forces all shards onto nodes\n# with attribute tier=hot.  Setting it to null removes the constraint.\n# '_tier_preference=data_content' was explicitly set; null removes it so\n# Elasticsearch falls back to its own allocation logic.\n#\n# NOTE: index.number_of_shards=3 CANNOT be reverted on an open index —\n# it is immutable.  To restore the default (1 shard) you must:\n#   1. Create a new index with number_of_shards=1\n#   2. Reindex: POST /_reindex { \"source\":{\"index\":\"audit-index\"}, \"dest\":{\"index\":\"audit-index-v2\"} }\n#   3. Delete audit-index and recreate as an alias if needed\n# This causes downtime/data-migration and is excluded from this script.\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"[1/3] Clearing custom routing allocation settings on 'audit-index'...\"\nRESPONSE=$(es_curl -X PUT \"${ES_SVC}/audit-index/_settings\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"index\": {\n      \"routing\": {\n        \"allocation\": {\n          \"require\": {\n            \"tier\": null\n          },\n          \"include\": {\n            \"_tier_preference\": null\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }')\necho \"  API response: ${RESPONSE}\"\necho \"${RESPONSE}\" | grep -q '\"acknowledged\":true' \\\n  && echo \"  OK: audit-index allocation settings cleared.\" \\\n  || { echo \"  ERROR: unexpected API response — aborting.\"; exit 1; }\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# STEP 2 — Remove node.attr.tier from the es-config ConfigMap\n#\n# node.attr.tier=hot is a STATIC node attribute set in elasticsearch.yml\n# (mounted from ConfigMap 'es-config').  It cannot be changed via the\n# Elasticsearch API — the ConfigMap must be patched and pods restarted.\n#\n# This step writes a new elasticsearch.yml (without the node.attr.tier\n# line) into the ConfigMap.  STEP 3 then restarts the pods to apply it.\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"\"\necho \"[2/3] Removing 'node.attr.tier: hot' from es-config ConfigMap...\"\n\n# Extract current elasticsearch.yml and strip the node.attr.tier line\nkubectl -n \"${NS}\" get configmap es-config \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.data.elasticsearch\\.yml}' \\\n  | grep -v '^node\\.attr\\.tier:' \\\n  > /tmp/elasticsearch-reverted.yml\n\necho \"  Revised elasticsearch.yml:\"\nsed 's/^/    /' /tmp/elasticsearch-reverted.yml\n\n# Replace the ConfigMap in-place\nkubectl -n \"${NS}\" create configmap es-config \\\n  --from-file=elasticsearch.yml=/tmp/elasticsearch-reverted.yml \\\n  --dry-run=client -o yaml \\\n  | kubectl -n \"${NS}\" replace -f -\necho \"  OK: es-config ConfigMap updated.\"\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# STEP 3 — Restart StatefulSet pods to pick up the updated elasticsearch.yml\n#\n# The StatefulSet uses updateStrategy=OnDelete, so pods must be manually\n# deleted.  We roll them one at a time and wait for each replacement to\n# become Ready before proceeding, to avoid a simultaneous quorum loss.\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"\"\necho \"[3/3] Rolling restart of es-cluster pods (OnDelete strategy)...\"\nPODS=$(kubectl -n \"${NS}\" get pods -l app=es-cluster -o name | sort)\nfor POD in ${PODS}; do\n  echo \"  Deleting ${POD} ...\"\n  kubectl -n \"${NS}\" delete \"${POD}\"\n  echo \"  Waiting for replacement pod to become Ready (timeout 180s)...\"\n  kubectl -n \"${NS}\" wait pod -l app=es-cluster \\\n    --for=condition=Ready --timeout=180s 2>/dev/null \\\n    && echo \"  OK: at least one pod Ready — proceeding.\" \\\n    || echo \"  WARN: wait timed out; inspect cluster health before continuing.\"\n  echo \"\"\ndone\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Final verification\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"===================================================================\"\necho \" Post-rollback state\"\necho \"===================================================================\"\necho \"\"\necho \"Cluster settings:\"\nes_curl \"${ES_SVC}/_cluster/settings?flat_settings=true\"\necho \"\"\necho \"audit-index settings (routing section):\"\nes_curl \"${ES_SVC}/audit-index/_settings?flat_settings=true\" \\\n  | grep -o '\"routing[^\"]*\":\"[^\"]*\"' || echo \"  (none)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"Node attributes:\"\nes_curl \"${ES_SVC}/_nodes?filter_path=nodes.*.attributes\"\necho \"\"\necho \"===================================================================\"\necho \" Rollback complete.\"\necho \"\"\necho \" Reverted:\"\necho \"   - audit-index: routing.allocation.require.tier removed\"\necho \"   - audit-index: routing.allocation.include._tier_preference removed\"\necho \"   - es-config:   node.attr.tier: hot removed from elasticsearch.yml\"\necho \"   - es-cluster pods restarted with updated node config\"\necho \"\"\necho \" NOT reverted (immutable without data loss):\"\necho \"   - audit-index: index.number_of_shards=3 (default=1)\"\necho \"     Manual steps required: reindex into new index, then delete+recreate.\"\necho \"===================================================================\"\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":670,"cache_read_input_tokens":37316,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":670},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a5b4a78-ed46-4e06-8aac-06a06e5ca78c","uuid":"0c759194-fb2b-41dc-828f-0830e5a392c5","request_id":"req_011Cc2f15ZEaGo4VX93pwBqg"}
